# <emoji> <module> > <description>
#
# IMPORTANT: All commit messages MUST be in English
#
# Types with emojis:
#   ✨ feat     (new feature)
#   🐛 fix      (bug fix)
#   📝 docs     (documentation changes)
#   💄 style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
#   ♻️  refactor (refactoring production code)
#   ⚡️ perf     (performance improvements)
#   ✅ test     (adding missing tests, refactoring tests)
#   🔧 chore    (updating grunt tasks etc; no production code change)
#   👷 ci       (changes to CI configuration files and scripts)
#   📦 build    (changes that affect the build system or dependencies)
#   🎨 ui       (user interface changes)
#   🔒 security (security improvements)
#   🚀 deploy   (deployment changes)
#
# Module examples: components, api, utils, auth, ui, etc.
#
# Description must:
# 1. Be in English
# 2. Use imperative mood ("add" not "added" or "adds")
# 3. Start with lowercase
# 4. Not end with a period
#
# Examples:
# ✨ components > add new theme switcher
# 🐛 api > fix user authentication flow
# ♻️ utils > refactor date formatting functions
#
# Message body:
# - Use bullet points for changes
# - Keep it short and clear
# - Focus on what changed
#
# Example body:
# - Add dark mode support
# - Implement theme persistence
# - Fix hydration issues
#
# Footer (optional):
# - Reference issues and PRs
# - BREAKING CHANGE: <description>
#
# VS Code Extensions:
# - Gitmoji (seatonjiang.gitmoji-vscode)
# - Conventional Commits (vivaxy.vscode-conventional-commits) 